# 1. Server Preparation

Update the server.

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y
```

Install required packages.

```bash
sudo apt install -y \
postfix \
postfix-pcre \
mailutils \
dovecot-core \
dovecot-imapd \
dovecot-pop3d \
dovecot-lmtpd \
certbot \
python3-certbot-nginx \
openssl
```

Verify installed versions.

```bash
postconf mail_version

dovecot --version
```

Expected:

```
Postfix 3.10.6
Dovecot 2.4.2
```

---

# 2. DNS Configuration

## A Record

```
mail.blessed.co.zw
↓

YOUR_SERVER_IP
```

## MX Record

```
Host:

@

Priority:

10

Target:

mail.blessed.co.zw
```

## SPF

```
v=spf1 include:spf.brevo.com ip4:SERVER_IP ~all
```

## DKIM

Use the DKIM record supplied by Brevo.

## DMARC

```
Host:

_dmarc

Value:

v=DMARC1; p=quarantine; rua=mailto:postmaster@blessed.co.zw
```

## Reverse DNS (PTR)

Configure at your VPS provider.

```
SERVER_IP

↓

mail.blessed.co.zw
```

Verify:

```bash
host SERVER_IP
```

Expected:

```
mail.blessed.co.zw
```

---

# Cloudflare

Mail records MUST be DNS Only.

Do NOT proxy:

- mail
- MX
- autodiscover
- autoconfig

Grey cloud only.

