# IMPORTANT FIX (Dovecot 2.4)

## Login using email addresses

Create

```
/etc/dovecot/conf.d/99-auth-custom.conf
```

Add

```conf
auth_username_format = %{user | username | lower}
```

Restart

```bash
sudo systemctl restart dovecot
```

Verify

```bash
sudo doveadm auth test info@blessed.co.zw
```

Expected

```
passdb: info auth succeeded

user=info
```

### IMPORTANT

Do NOT use

```conf
auth_username_format = %n
```

or

```conf
auth_username_format = %Ln
```

These older formats were interpreted literally by Dovecot 2.4.2 during our deployment, resulting in authentication failures such as:

```
user=%n
```

or

```
user=%Ln
```

The working configuration is:

```conf
auth_username_format = %{user | username | lower}
```

